    "en": {
      "title": "20,000 crore outstanding bills get stuck in the exchequer",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sources in the Ministry of Finance state that outstanding bills of around twenty thousand crores of rupees have been stuck in the treasury for the projects carried out in the past across the country.",
        ". It is also said that the bills of about 8000 crore rupees were submitted by the contractors who built the highways.",
        "In addition, it is reported that the bills of crores of rupees presented by the Ministries of Health, Housing, Urban Development, Education etc. are also stuck in the Treasury.",
        "It is known that finding money to pay these outstanding bills has been a serious problem since about two or three years ago.",
        "Due to this, it is known that the contractors are also facing a serious problem.",
        "It has been learned that President Ranil Wickramasinghe has also stated in the ruling party meeting that there is a problem with paying the contractors who built the highways."
      ],
